creature-listener (0.3.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * YAML config file support (--config-path), matching creature-agent pattern.
  * System prompt, LLM settings, creature ID, wake word models, VAD, and
    tracing are all configurable via the YAML file.
  * CLI simplified to --config-path plus a handful of overrides for dev/testing.
  * Sample config installed to /etc/creature-listener.yaml in .deb package.
  * systemd service uses config file instead of env var expansion.

 -- April White <april@creature.engineering>  Tue, 25 Mar 2026 22:30:00 +0000

creature-listener (0.2.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add OpenTelemetry distributed tracing with OTLP HTTP export to Honeycomb.
  * Propagate W3C traceparent headers to creature-server for end-to-end traces.
  * Spans for each conversation phase: stt.transcribe, llm.respond,
    server.streaming_session, all under a root conversation.turn span.
  * Replace Porcupine wake word with LOWWI (openWakeWord ONNX models) —
    fully open source, no API key or account required.
  * Support HONEYCOMB_API_KEY env var and --honeycomb-api-key CLI flag.
  * Static link all FetchContent deps except ONNX Runtime for clean packaging.
  * Fix null content handling in LLM SSE stream parsing.

 -- April White <april@creature.engineering>  Tue, 25 Mar 2026 06:00:00 +0000

creature-listener (0.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.
  * PortAudio 16kHz mono audio capture with device selection.
  * Porcupine wake word detection (optional, keyboard fallback).
  * Energy-based voice activity detection with adaptive noise floor.
  * whisper.cpp STT (tiny.en model) with hallucination filtering.
  * Streaming LLM client (llama-server SSE) with sentence splitting.
  * Conversation history with configurable max exchanges.
  * creature-server streaming session integration (ad-hoc-stream API).
  * Verbose/debug logging flag.

 -- April White <april@creature.engineering>  Mon, 24 Mar 2026 21:00:00 +0000
